Data Preprocessing

  • Load data

  • Handle TKT

  • Create Interaction Terms

  • Manually assigning categorical variable types

  • Reset reference variables(levels) for dummy variables

  • Define SMSB (SMS Binary variable): 1 for 128 and 516, 0 for 515

  • Define some new interactions (02/15/2021)

  • Finally form shell_data

data_file = "Master_TCAD_Final_20210109_shell_assumed less severe acc_recover_rev.csv"
data_shell_subset <- read.csv(data_file)

# Handle TKT
data_shell_subset <- data_shell_subset %>%
  mutate(TKT = replace(TKT, (Is.TSP.Assumed==1) + (Is.CDR.Assumed==1) +
                         (Is.FCI.assumed==1) > 0, 2))

# Create Interaction Terms
data_shell_subset <- data_shell_subset %>%
  mutate(TSP_IOF = TSP * IOF) %>%
  mutate(IOF_IOFB = IOF * IOFB) %>%
  mutate(TCL_TCLB = TCL * TCLB) %>%
  mutate(TCLsubFCI = TCL - FCI) %>%
  mutate(TSP_CDR = TSP * CDR) %>%
  mutate(TSPC_CDR = TSPC * CDR) %>%
  mutate(EIS_CDR = EIS.N * CDR)

# Manually assigning categorical variable types
cat_vars = c("JKT", "TKT", "ACT", "HMS", "SMS", 
             "THT", "TFP", "TFN", "TFPB", 
             "IOFB", "TCLB")
data_shell_subset[, cat_vars] = lapply(data_shell_subset[, cat_vars],
                                          factor)

# Reset reference variables(levels) for dummy variables
data_shell_subset <- data_shell_subset %>%
  mutate(JKT = relevel(JKT, ref="0")) %>%
  mutate(ACT = relevel(ACT, ref="1")) %>%
  mutate(THT = relevel(THT, ref="0")) %>%
  mutate(SMS = relevel(SMS, ref="515")) %>%
  mutate(TFP = relevel(TFP, ref="U")) %>%
  mutate(TFN = relevel(TFN, ref="1")) %>%
  mutate(HMS = relevel(HMS, ref="515")) %>%
  mutate(TFPB = relevel(TFPB, ref="0"))

# Define `SMSB` (SMS Binary variable): 1 for 128 and 516, 0 for 515
data_shell_subset <- data_shell_subset %>%
  mutate(SMSB = ifelse(SMS == '515', 0, 1)) 

# New interactions defined on 02/15/2021
data_shell_subset <- data_shell_subset %>%
  mutate(TSPS = TSP * TSP) %>% 
  mutate(EISS = EIS.N * EIS.N) %>% 
  mutate(TSPS_CDR = TSPS * CDR) %>% 
  mutate(EIS_IOF = EIS.N * IOF) %>% 
  mutate(TSPS_IOF = TSPS * IOF) %>% 
  mutate(TSPC_IOF = TSPC * IOF) %>% 
  mutate(EISS_IOF = EISS * IOF) %>% 
  mutate(EISS_CDR = EISS * CDR)
  • Check for Missing Values in TKT? No missing values.
data_shell_subset$TKT[is.na(data_shell_subset$TKT)]=1
sum(is.na(data_shell_subset$TKT))
  • Construct the data set for shell analysis shell_data. Further split into training data train_shell (80%) and testing data test_shell (20%)
var_names <- c("TSPS", "EISS", "TSP_CDR", "TSPS_CDR", "EIS_IOF", "TSP",
               "CDR", "JKT", "IOF", "TSP_IOF", "EIS.N", "TWT", "TKT",
               "ACT", "STS", "SID", "THT", "EIS_CDR", "Z.indicator", "LDLS")
shell_data <- data_shell_subset %>%
  filter(SUBS==1) %>%
  select(all_of(var_names))

set.seed(1231)

train_id <- shell_data$LDLS %>%
  createDataPartition(p=0.8,list=FALSE)
train_shell <- shell_data[train_id, ]
test_shell <- shell_data[-train_id, ]

Lasso

Use glmnet package to fit a logistic regression model with Lasso penalty on train_shell, produce the CV plot, and report coefficients based on lambda.min and lambda.1se and produce a path plot.

shell_x <- model.matrix(LDLS ~ ., data = train_shell)[,-1]
shell_y <- train_shell$LDLS

shell_cv.lasso <- cv.glmnet(shell_x, shell_y, alpha = 1, family = "binomial")
small.lambda.min.betas <- coef(shell_cv.lasso, s = "lambda.min")
small.lambda.1se.betas <- coef(shell_cv.lasso, s = "lambda.1se")

CV-Lasso

Repeatedly (m = 10 times) apply glmnet with Lasso on a subset (80%) of the data, record the corresponding coefficients in two matrices and then report the mean and frequency (of being non-zero).

m = 10 # Number of iterations
ncoefs_min = NULL  # coefs with lambda_min
ncoefs_1se = NULL  # coefs with lambda_1se
shell_x <- model.matrix(LDLS ~ ., data = shell_data)[,-1]
shell_y <- shell_data$LDLS

for(i in 1:m){
  tmp_id = shell_data$LDLS %>%
    createDataPartition(p=0.8, list=FALSE)
  tmp_x <- shell_x[tmp_id, ]
  tmp_y <- shell_y[tmp_id]

  tmp_cv.lasso <- cv.glmnet(tmp_x, tmp_y, 
                              alpha = 1, family = "binomial")
  
  small.lambda.min.betas <- coef(tmp_cv.lasso, s = "lambda.min")
  small.lambda.1se.betas <- coef(tmp_cv.lasso, s = "lambda.1se")
  
  ncoefs_min=cbind(ncoefs_min, small.lambda.min.betas)
  ncoefs_1se=cbind(ncoefs_1se, small.lambda.1se.betas)
}

colnames(ncoefs_min) = NULL
colnames(ncoefs_1se) = NULL

avgcoefs <- data.frame(
  ave_min = rowMeans(ncoefs_min),  
  freq_min = rowMeans(ncoefs_min != 0),
  ave_1se = rowMeans(ncoefs_1se),  
  freq_1se = rowMeans(ncoefs_1se != 0))

r2Log <- function(model) {
  summaryLog <- summary(model)
  1 - summaryLog$deviance / summaryLog$null.deviance
}

Prediction

    1. Fit a shared logistic model with selected variables on all shell data shell_data, and then form prediction on five new cars.
    1. For each of the five test cars, fit a separate logistic model on a subset of the data (similar to that particular test car’s features) and form prediction.
  • Note that the features used in the two approaches are slightly different. For example, in approach 2), we add features TWT=10000 and TKT=1, and drop features JKT and THT.
# Construct newcars data frame with features for the five test cars
newcars = data.frame(
  TSP = rep(26, 5), 
  CDR = rep(11, 5), 
  JKT = c('0', rep('1', 4)),
  IOF = rep(6, 5), 
  TSP_IOF = rep(156, 5), 
  EIS.N = rep(16.5, 5), 
  ACT = rep('1', 5), 
  STS = c(rep(0.4375, 3), 0.5625, 0.625),
  SID = rep(119, 5), 
  THT = c('0', rep('1', 4)),
  EIS_CDR = rep(181.5, 5), 
  Z.indicator = rep(0, 5), 
  TWT = rep(10000, 5), 
  TKT = rep('1', 5))
rownames(newcars) = c('nojacket_111', 'jacket_111', '117R', '117J', '5')
  
newcars_pred = data.frame(matrix(NA, nrow=5, 2))
rownames(newcars_pred) = rownames(newcars)
colnames(newcars_pred) = c("Shared_Model", "Separate_Models")

# 1) Fit one shared model
shell_lasso_vars <- c('TSP', 'CDR', 'JKT', 'IOF', 'TSP_IOF', 'EIS.N', 
                      # 'TWT', 'TKT', 
                      'ACT', 'STS', 'SID', 'THT', 'EIS_CDR', 'Z.indicator')
shell_data_logit <- glm(formula = LDLS ~ .,
                        family = binomial, 
                        data = shell_data[, c('LDLS', shell_lasso_vars)])
newcars_pred[, 1] <- predict(shell_data_logit, newcars, type="response")

# 2) Fit five separate models

car1_subset <- shell_data %>% filter(JKT=="0" & THT=="0")
car2_subset <- shell_data %>% filter(JKT=="1" & THT=="1")
car3_subset <- shell_data %>% filter(JKT=="1" & STS < 0.5 & THT=="1") 
car4_subset <- shell_data %>% filter(JKT=="1" & STS >= 0.5 & STS<0.6 & THT=="1") 
car5_subset <- shell_data %>% filter(JKT=="1" & STS>=0.6 & THT=="0")

tmp_vars <- c('TSP', 'CDR', 'IOF', 'TSP_IOF', 'EIS.N',
              'TWT', 'TKT', 'ACT', 'EIS_CDR')
car1_logit <- glm(LDLS ~ ., family = binomial, 
                  data = car1_subset[, c('LDLS', tmp_vars)])
car2_logit <- glm(LDLS ~ ., family = binomial, 
                  data = car2_subset[, c('LDLS', tmp_vars)])

                  data = car4_subset[, c('LDLS', tmp_vars)])
